<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="508" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1266,1975]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1266,1291]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Yellow species; descendant plate of the anterior cercus hourglass-shaped in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1423,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[1391,1423,1267,1291]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
); phallus with narrow base, wider at mostly, with large dorsal subapical appendix (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1142,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[1110,1142,1303,1327]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="508" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1266,1975]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,415,1338,1363]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[432,517,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[486,517,1339,1363]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[540,604,1338,1363]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Head</emphasis>
: Face of sides slightly diverging toward the proboscis, brown with gray pruinescence visible in ventral view, about 
<date box="[639,674,1374,1399]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
<number box="[639,652,1374,1399]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="5.0">5</number>
X
</date>
longer than lower width. Ocellar tubercle protruberant, brown with brown pruinescence; ocelli yellow. Antenna yellow with black bristles; postpedicel about 
<date box="[1169,1204,1411,1435]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
<number box="[1169,1182,1411,1435]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
longer than pedicel; stylus about 
<date box="[298,332,1447,1471]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
<number box="[298,311,1447,1471]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
longer than postpedicel. Proboscis yellow shorter than head height. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1123,1212,1446,1471]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Thorax</emphasis>
yellow, shiny (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,182,1483,1507]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs yellow, except brown apical ring on hind femur and all tarsomeres 
<number box="[1016,1058,1482,1507]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
brown; hind tibia and tarsus with anterodorsal and posterodorsal rows of longer bristles. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[780,845,1518,1543]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[862,945,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[916,945,1519,1543]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) hyaline; pterostigma brown, conspicuous, about 
<number box="[222,257,1555,1579]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="2.8">2.8</number>
X longer than wide. Halter pale yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[718,835,1554,1579]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Abdomen</emphasis>
yellow, shiny (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1145,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Figs 17, 19</figureCitation>
); tergite 
<number box="[1248,1262,1555,1579]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="8.0">8</number>
divided in two subrectangular plates; sternite 
<number box="[494,508,1591,1615]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="8.0">8</number>
divided in two subrectangular plates. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[938,1069,1590,1615]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Terminalia</emphasis>
: Anterior cercus with proclinate dorsal projection in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[528,612,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[581,612,1627,1651]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
), concave in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[911,995,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[964,995,1627,1651]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
); descendant plate hourglass-shaped in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[328,413,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[381,413,1663,1687]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Posterior cercus with acuminate apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1038,1122,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[1091,1122,1663,1687]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
), without dorsal projections (
<figureCitation box="[159,249,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[218,249,1699,1723]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypoproct subtriangular in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[764,851,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,418,1772]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,407,1781]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 16. Opeatocerata agudeloi sp. nov., holotype ♂. 8. habitus, lateral view; 9. wing; 10. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 11. Terminalia; 12. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 13. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 14. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 15. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 16. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252521/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[822,851,1699,1723]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
) and comma-shaped in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1424,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1424,1699,1723]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrial ventral lobe slightly bilobed at apex (
<figureCitation box="[709,797,1734,1759]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[765,797,1735,1759]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
); spiniform bristles mesially on dorsal lobe and longer bristles apically on ventral lobe (
<figureCitation box="[516,600,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[568,600,1771,1795]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium longer than wide, with rounded apex and median sinus (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,182,1806,1831]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
), without long bristles. Phallus with narrow base, wider at mostly, longer than hypandrium with large dorsal subapical appendix (
<figureCitation box="[381,465,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[433,465,1843,1867]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subepandrial sclerite wider than long, U-shaped (
