<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="510" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="510">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,583,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="510">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[325,614,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Opeatocerata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ampullaria" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[325,614,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="510">Opeatocerata ampullaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[624,717,583,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="510" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[624,717,583,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="510">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from other species by the descendant plate of anterior cercus hourglass-shaped in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[645,731,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,193,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Opeatocerata ampullaria sp. nov., holotype ♂. 17. habitus, lateral view; 18. wing; 19. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 20. terminalia, lateral view; 21. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 22. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 23. subepandrial and bacilliform sclerites, dorsal view; 24. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 25. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252522/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="510">
Fig. 
<number box="[700,731,620,644]" pageId="8" pageNumber="510" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
), which is subrectangular, subtriangular or with latero-ventral projection in other species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
